osed_at": "2019-10-05T09:09:30Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The use case:  in a chat with @effigies and @nellh on how to possibly organize openneuro derivatives, @nellh expressed desire to use `datalad run` and I tried to recommend our YODA organization where we would do something like\r\n\r\n```\r\ndatalad create derivative-ds\r\ndatalad install -d derivative-ds --source URL-to-raw-dataset sourcedata\r\ndatalad (containers-)run --input derivative-ds/sourcedata --output derivative-ds/ bids-app bids-app-params\r\n```\r\nThe point is that input is a subfolder within derivative-ds/, which we do not really want to unlock as part of the `output` and then the derivative-ds, but we would like to be able to say that everything produced in that dataset is produced by that command (e.g. fmriprep, etc).\r\n\r\nMay be it would somehow just work out because sourcedata/ is the subdataset, so it would not get unlocked recursively?", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2923/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laug